Organization of Data Objects

The objects in the workspace object CRC_BMI_DATA.RData are organized as follows. The lists below are split based on the sequencing type. All objects have been put into a phyloseq objects based on the phyloseq package. * 16S sequencing data objects + OTU Table (otu_table) - Rows are taxa names - Columns are samples + Taxanomic Table (tax_table) - Rows are same ad the OTU Table with all taxa names - Columns are which level of the taxonomy and what the name under that taxa. + Sample Data (sam_data) - gives details of each sample (meta-data) - identifiers for subsetting based on BMI or other group + Phylogenic Tree (phy_tree) * WGS data objects + OTU Table (otu_table) - Rows are taxa names - Columns are samples + Sample Data * Pooled Data + Contains the taxonomy of all samples from all studies included + Sample data contains BMI, BMI Category and Cancer identifier

Alpha diversity in Obese vs Non-Obese with or without CRC

my_phylo <- myphylo
datasets <- names(myphylo)

# Estimate alpha diversity metrics: this loop also combines the etimates
# with the sample data to create a dataframe for each study that includes
# alpha diversity
estAlpha <- list()
bp_CRC <- list()
bp_nonCRC <- list()
man_U_Tests <- list()
for (df in datasets) {
    # df <- 'baxter'
    dat <- prune_species(speciesSums(my_phylo[[df]]) > 1, my_phylo[[df]])
    
    estAlpha[[df]] <- estimate_richness(dat, measures = c("Observed", "Shannon", 
        "InvSimpson"))
    
    # Faith's phylogenetic diversity metric Not supported by phyloseq package
    # Need phylogenetic tree if(df == 'baxter'| df = 'zackular'| df =
    # 'zeller.Stool'| df = 'zeller.Tissue'){ estAlpha[[df]]$faithPD <-
    # pd(stored_dat[[df]]$otu.tab, stored_dat[[df]]$tree) }
    
    
    estAlpha[[df]] <- cbind(sample_data(dat), estAlpha[[df]])
    
    # boxplots for alpha by CRC and non-CRC subset to CRC
    subdat <- na.omit(estAlpha[[df]][estAlpha[[df]]$Status == "CRC", ])
    
    bp_CRC[[paste0(df, ".", "Observed")]] <- ggplot(subdat, aes(x = BMI_Cat, 
        y = Observed)) + geom_boxplot(outlier.alpha = 0, aes(color = BMI_Cat)) + 
        geom_point(alpha = 0.5, aes(fill = BMI_Cat, color = BMI_Cat), position = position_jitterdodge()) + 
        ylim(0, 600) + theme_minimal() + coord_flip()
    
    bp_CRC[[paste0(df, ".", "Shannon")]] <- ggplot(subdat, aes(x = BMI_Cat, 
        y = Shannon)) + geom_boxplot(outlier.alpha = 0, aes(color = BMI_Cat)) + 
        geom_point(alpha = 0.5, aes(fill = BMI_Cat, color = BMI_Cat), position = position_jitterdodge()) + 
        ylim(0, 5) + theme_minimal() + coord_flip()
    
    man_U_Tests[[paste0(df, ".", "CRC", ".", "Observed")]] <- wilcox.test(Observed ~ 
        BMI_Cat, data = subdat)
    man_U_Tests[[paste0(df, ".", "CRC", ".", "Shannon")]] <- wilcox.test(Shannon ~ 
        BMI_Cat, data = subdat)
    
    # subset to Non-CRC
    subdat <- estAlpha[[df]][estAlpha[[df]]$Status != "CRC", ]
    
    bp_nonCRC[[paste0(df, ".", "Observed")]] <- ggplot(subdat, aes(BMI_Cat, 
        Observed)) + geom_boxplot(outlier.alpha = 0, aes(color = BMI_Cat)) + 
        geom_point(alpha = 0.5, aes(fill = BMI_Cat, color = BMI_Cat), position = position_jitterdodge()) + 
        ylim(0, 600) + theme_minimal() + coord_flip()
    
    bp_nonCRC[[paste0(df, ".", "Shannon")]] <- ggplot(subdat, aes(x = BMI_Cat, 
        y = Shannon)) + geom_boxplot(outlier.alpha = 0, aes(color = BMI_Cat)) + 
        geom_point(alpha = 0.5, aes(fill = BMI_Cat, color = BMI_Cat), position = position_jitterdodge()) + 
        ylim(0, 5) + theme_minimal() + coord_flip()
    
    man_U_Tests[[paste0(df, ".", "nonCRC", ".", "Observed")]] <- wilcox.test(Observed ~ 
        BMI_Cat, data = subdat)
    man_U_Tests[[paste0(df, ".", "nonCRC", ".", "Shannon")]] <- wilcox.test(Shannon ~ 
        BMI_Cat, data = subdat)
}  # End make Box plots

Results from Man-Whitney-U Tests

type <- c("CRC", "nonCRC")

results.mwu <- matrix(0, nrow = 16, ncol = 2)
i <- 1
for (df in datasets) {
    for (ty in type) {
        
        results.mwu[i, ] <- as.matrix(c(man_U_Tests[[paste0(df, ".", ty, ".", 
            "Observed")]]$p.value, man_U_Tests[[paste0(df, ".", ty, ".", "Shannon")]]$p.value), 
            ncol = 2)
        i = i + 1
    }
}

row.names(results.mwu) <- c("baxter.CRC", "baxter.nonCRC", "zackular.CRC", "zackular.nonCRC", 
    "zeller.Stool.CRC", "zeller.Stool.nonCRC", "zeller.Tissue.CRC", "zeller.Tissue.nonCRC", 
    "feng.CRC", "feng.nonCRC", "voghtmann.CRC", "voghtmann.nonCRC", "zeller.WGS.CRC", 
    "zeller.WGS.nonCRC", "Pooled.CRC", "Pooled.nonCRC")
colnames(results.mwu) <- c("Observed", "Shannon")
results.mwu <- round(results.mwu, 3)
print(results.mwu)

Supplemental Figure 1: Scatterplots

sp_CRC <- list()
sp_nonCRC <- list()
for(df in datasets)
{
    # subset to CRC
    subdat <- na.omit(estAlpha[[df]][estAlpha[[df]]$Status == "CRC",])

    sp_CRC[[paste0(df, ".","Observed")]] <- ggplot(subdat, aes(x = BMI, y = Observed, color = BMI_Cat)) +
        geom_point(alpha = .5, aes(color = BMI_Cat)) +
        #geom_smooth(method=lm,se=FALSE,fullrange=TRUE) +
        ylim(0, 600) +
        xlim(10, 50) +
        theme_bw()
    
    sp_CRC[[paste0(df, ".","Shannon")]] <- ggplot(subdat, aes(x = BMI, y = Shannon, color = BMI_Cat)) +
        geom_point(alpha = .5, aes(color = BMI_Cat)) +
        #geom_smooth(method=lm,se=FALSE,fullrange=TRUE) +
        ylim(0, 5) +
      xlim(10, 50) +
        theme_bw() 
    # subset to Non-CRC
    subdat <- estAlpha[[df]][estAlpha[[df]]$Status != "CRC",]

    sp_nonCRC[[paste0(df, ".","Observed")]] <- ggplot(subdat, aes(BMI, Observed, color = BMI_Cat)) +
        geom_point(alpha = .5, aes(color = BMI_Cat)) +
        #geom_smooth(method=lm,se=FALSE,fullrange=TRUE) +
        ylim(0, 600) +
      xlim(10, 50) +
        theme_bw()
      
    sp_nonCRC[[paste0(df, ".","Shannon")]] <- ggplot(subdat, aes(x = BMI, y = Shannon, color = BMI_Cat)) +
        geom_point(alpha = .5, aes(color = BMI_Cat)) +
        #geom_smooth(method=lm,se=FALSE,fullrange=TRUE) +
        ylim(0, 5) +
      xlim(10, 50) +
        theme_bw()
} # End make scatter
